{"title":"Model Deployment Quick Reference Guide","html":"<h1 id=\"model-deployment-quick-reference-guide\">Model Deployment Quick Reference Guide</h1>\n<p>Quick reference for deploying ML models.</p>\n<h2 id=\"table-of-contents\">Table of Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#model-serialization\">Model Serialization</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#api-frameworks\">API Frameworks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#docker-commands\">Docker Commands</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#cloud-platforms\">Cloud Platforms</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#common-issues-solutions\">Common Issues &amp; Solutions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#best-practices-checklist\">Best Practices Checklist</a></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"model-serialization\">Model Serialization</h2>\n<h3 id=\"save-models\">Save Models</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># Scikit-learn</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">joblib.dump(model, </span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'model.joblib'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># Keras</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">model.save(</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'model.h5'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># PyTorch</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">torch.save(model.state_dict(), </span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'model.pth'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"api-frameworks\">API Frameworks</h2>\n<h3 id=\"fastapi\">FastAPI</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">from</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> fastapi </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> FastAPI</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">app = FastAPI()</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">@app.post</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">\"/predict\"</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6\">async</span><span style=\"color:#569CD6\"> def</span><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\"> predict</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(</span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">features</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: list[</span><span style=\"color:#4EC9B0\">float</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">]):</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> {</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">\"prediction\"</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: model.predict([features])[</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">0</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">]}</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"flask\">Flask</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">from</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> flask </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> Flask, jsonify</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">app = Flask(</span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">__name__</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">@app.route</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'/predict'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">, </span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">methods</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">=[</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'POST'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">])</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6\">def</span><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\"> predict</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">():</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> jsonify({</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">'prediction'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: model.predict([features])[</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">0</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">]})</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"docker-commands\">Docker Commands</h2>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># Build</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">docker</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#569CD6\"> -t</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> ml-api</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> .</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># Run</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">docker</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#569CD6\"> -p</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> 8000:8000</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> ml-api</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\"># Compose</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">docker-compose</span><span style=\"color:#CE9178\"> up</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"a-b-testing\">A/B Testing</h2>\n<h3 id=\"statistical-significance\">Statistical Significance</h3>\n<pre class=\"shiki dark-plus\" style=\"background-color:#1E1E1E;color:#D4D4D4\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">from</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> scipy </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> stats</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">import</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> numpy </span><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">as</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> np</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#569CD6\">def</span><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\"> analyze_ab_test</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(</span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">conversions_a</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">, </span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">total_a</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">, </span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">conversions_b</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">, </span><span style=\"color:#9CDCFE\">total_b</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">):</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">    \"\"\"Z-test for two proportions\"\"\"</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    rate_a = conversions_a / total_a</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    rate_b = conversions_b / total_b</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    </span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\">    # Pooled proportion</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    pooled = (conversions_a + conversions_b) / (total_a + total_b)</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    se = np.sqrt(pooled * (</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">1</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> - pooled) * (</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">1</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">/total_a + </span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">1</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">/total_b))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    </span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A9955\">    # Z-score and p-value</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    z = (rate_b - rate_a) / se</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    p_value = </span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">2</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> * (</span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">1</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> - stats.norm.cdf(</span><span style=\"color:#DCDCAA\">abs</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">(z)))</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    </span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#C586C0\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\"> {</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">        'rate_a'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: rate_a,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">        'rate_b'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: rate_b,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">        'p_value'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: p_value,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#CE9178\">        'significant'</span><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">: p_value &#x3C; </span><span style=\"color:#B5CEA8\">0.05</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D4D4D4\">    }</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"></span></code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"best-practices\">Best Practices</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Clear hypothesis</strong>: Define what you're testing</li>\n<li><strong>Primary metric</strong>: One clear success metric</li>\n<li><strong>Sample size</strong>: Ensure statistical power</li>\n<li><strong>Don't peek early</strong>: Avoid stopping prematurely</li>\n<li><strong>Monitor</strong>: Track deployed model performance</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"cloud-platforms\">Cloud Platforms</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Platform</th>\n<th>Use Case</th>\n<th>Command</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><strong>Heroku</strong></td>\n<td>Simple</td>\n<td><code>git push heroku main</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>AWS Lambda</strong></td>\n<td>Serverless</td>\n<td>Deploy via console/CLI</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>GCP Cloud Run</strong></td>\n<td>Containers</td>\n<td><code>gcloud run deploy</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Azure</strong></td>\n<td>Enterprise</td>\n<td><code>az container create</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>AWS SageMaker</strong></td>\n<td>ML Platform</td>\n<td><code>sagemaker.deploy()</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"common-issues-amp-solutions\">Common Issues &amp; Solutions</h2>\n<h3 id=\"issue-1-model-too-large\">Issue 1: Model Too Large</h3>\n<p><strong>Solution</strong>: Quantize, prune, use smaller models</p>\n<h3 id=\"issue-2-slow-response\">Issue 2: Slow Response</h3>\n<p><strong>Solution</strong>: Optimize model, use caching, batch processing</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"best-practices-checklist\">Best Practices Checklist</h2>\n<ul>\n<li> Validate all inputs</li>\n<li> Handle errors gracefully</li>\n<li> Add health checks</li>\n<li> Use HTTPS in production</li>\n<li> Monitor performance</li>\n<li> Version your models</li>\n<li> Document API</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Remember</strong>: Deployment is as important as training!</p>\n","source":"13-model-deployment/deployment-quick-reference.md","githubUrl":"https://github.com/NabidAlam/road-to-machine-learning/blob/main/13-model-deployment/deployment-quick-reference.md","module":"13-model-deployment","lessonId":"deployment-quick-reference","guideId":null,"type":"module"}